OL,3,C'It's because we care': Families
OL,4,Cfighting for justice after maternity
OL,5,Cfailings
OL,7,FITV News Central asked Health
OL,8,FSecretary Victoria Atkins and the
OL,9,FMinister for Women's Health Maria
OL,10,FCaulfield to answer that question, and
OL,11,Fexplain what the government is doing
OL,12,Fto address the concerns of families.
OL,14,FThey both refused - despite sending a
OL,15,Fstatement insisting that ensuring all
OL,16,Fwomen receive safe and compassionate
OL,17,Fmaternity care was a "priority".
OL,19,FITV News Central also approached the
OL,20,FCare Quality Commission (CQC) and NHS
OL,21,FEngland for comment, but they declined.
